[Thunder Rumbling]

03:26.720 --> 03:28.847
[Jay Leno Over TV] Any guys here
taking this Viagra? Let's see.

03:28.922 --> 03:30.981
- Not one honest guy.
- [Audience Laughs]

03:31.057 --> 03:33.787
Have you--
Okay?

03:33.860 --> 03:37.626
You know, you have to be--
A friend of mine dropped one of
these Viagra pills on the floor...

03:37.697 --> 03:40.427
- and his dog swallowed it.
- [Laughter]

03:40.500 --> 03:43.025
- Now he has a pointer. Anyway--
- [Laughter]

03:45.472 --> 03:49.067
- We have to talk about this.
- I know. You're right.

03:49.142 --> 03:51.770
[TV Continues, Indistinct]

03:51.845 --> 03:54.075
But do you really think
we can save this marriage...

03:54.147 --> 03:57.139
now that I've decided I like Leno
better than Letterman?

03:57.217 --> 04:00.550
[Sobs] Don't. I'm sorry.

04:00.620 --> 04:03.555
I remember when my jokes
used to make you laugh.

04:03.623 --> 04:05.557
They do. I just--

04:10.730 --> 04:14.723
- We have to talk about this.
- There's nothing to talk about.

04:14.801 --> 04:17.861
Oh, of course there is.

04:17.938 --> 04:19.872
But I don't want to.

04:23.410 --> 04:25.344
Okay.

04:28.315 --> 04:30.249
What about the party?

04:30.317 --> 04:32.911
Well, nothing's changed.
I have a brain tumor...

04:32.986 --> 04:35.716
but I'm going to that party,
with or without you.

04:35.789 --> 04:38.314
We've put a deposit down.

04:40.126 --> 04:42.060
Mission accomplished.

04:45.599 --> 04:46.657
- [Man] I am in love.

04:47.400 --> 04:48.890
- [Woman] In love?

04:48.969 --> 04:50.903
Yes, in love.

04:50.971 --> 04:54.407
But before we go further,
let me say this.

04:54.474 --> 04:58.171
Before we go...
further--

04:58.244 --> 05:02.613
- [Giggles]
- [Groans] I can't go any further.

05:02.682 --> 05:06.448
[Woman]
It's almost 1:00, Meredith. 1:00.

05:06.519 --> 05:10.455
- And I got a day job, remember?
- Yeah. Phil needs his sleep.
He's a postal worker.

05:10.523 --> 05:12.718
All right, slackers.
Trot off home.

05:13.793 --> 05:16.091
[Phil] Good night.

05:16.162 --> 05:19.029
- Settle a bet I have with Phillip?
- Yeah.

05:19.099 --> 05:22.296
He claims you have
no personal life whatsoever.

05:22.369 --> 05:24.496
I say that's impossible.

05:24.571 --> 05:27.165
I hope it wasn't a large bet.

05:27.240 --> 05:30.141
On equity waiver salary
you can't afford to lose much.

05:30.210 --> 05:32.144
No Mr. Right?

05:33.279 --> 05:35.713
Ms. Right?

05:35.782 --> 05:39.377
No inclination for either at the moment.
Thank you very much.

05:39.452 --> 05:43.149
But if you're fishing,
"mister" is my gender of choice.

05:43.223 --> 05:46.624
You're a wonderful person.
You should have someone in your life.

05:46.693 --> 05:48.627
That's all I'm saying.

05:48.695 --> 05:53.359
I can still be a wonderful person
and not have anybody in my life.

05:53.433 --> 05:56.425
Look, I'm just not interested
in a relationship right now.

05:56.503 --> 05:58.437
You are such a liar.

05:59.906 --> 06:02.704
I am such a liar.

06:11.685 --> 06:14.279
[Man] Front desk.

06:14.354 --> 06:16.288
Hold that, please!

06:20.727 --> 06:25.130
[Sighs] Did she not say,
"Hold that, please"?
Or isn't English your first language?

06:29.869 --> 06:31.962
[Speaking Japanese]

06:38.578 --> 06:40.512
Any trouble getting away?

06:40.580 --> 06:42.810
He has his acting class tonight.

06:42.882 --> 06:46.545
- You want me to get champagne?
- I don't think I have time for that.

06:48.421 --> 06:51.481
In case you're planning on
being gentle tonight...

06:52.492 --> 06:54.323
don't be.

07:39.873 --> 07:41.807
Mom?

07:44.043 --> 07:46.568
Welcome to Chicago.

07:48.314 --> 07:51.545
- You look awful.
- [Laughs]

07:51.618 --> 07:55.418
- You should get some sleep.
- I'll sleep when you sleep.

08:03.630 --> 08:05.791
[Hugh] It happened three days ago.

08:05.865 --> 08:10.097
The last time I talked with her--
my wife Leann--

08:11.271 --> 08:13.398
It was about 3:00.

08:13.473 --> 08:17.466
She was taking our son Jamey
to, uh, soccer practice.

08:17.544 --> 08:19.739
[Chuckles]

08:19.813 --> 08:24.182
Uh, I had a meeting at a bar.

08:24.250 --> 08:28.584
I'd had a few drinks. No more
than usual-- standard four-drink buzz.

08:28.655 --> 08:30.589
Maybe five.

08:32.325 --> 08:37.159
After, I was gonna meet Leann and Jamey
at the Pizza Hut.

08:38.932 --> 08:41.491
Every Tuesday night
Jamey wants Pizza Hut.

08:43.236 --> 08:45.636
So I was late.

08:45.705 --> 08:48.105
I was driving fast.

08:48.174 --> 08:51.803
Not too fast, I think.

08:53.346 --> 08:56.281
The light, it just turned.

08:58.251 --> 09:00.185
It was red for only a second.

09:00.253 --> 09:02.278
Less than.
I swear.

09:04.891 --> 09:06.825
I ran the light.

09:09.762 --> 09:11.889
I saw the car.

09:11.965 --> 09:14.593
I hit my wife's car.

09:14.667 --> 09:16.601
Oh, my God.

09:16.669 --> 09:20.605
I saw her face through the windshield
just as I hit them.

09:23.109 --> 09:26.101
She saw me.

09:26.179 --> 09:28.841
She knew it was me.

09:30.049 --> 09:31.983
Oh.

09:33.319 --> 09:35.344
You shouldn't be alone.

09:36.723 --> 09:38.748
Yes, I should.

09:38.825 --> 09:41.316
I should be alone in hell.

09:41.394 --> 09:43.328
That's where I am.

10:16.129 --> 10:20.589
Twenty minutes at 350 degrees
is absolutely essential.

10:20.667 --> 10:22.692
No more, no less.

10:22.769 --> 10:26.398
And the delicacy of this fish
is best appreciated by its taste...

10:26.472 --> 10:29.703
not necessarily by its appearance.

10:29.776 --> 10:31.801
Once you remove the fish
from the oven...

10:33.813 --> 10:37.078
transfer it directly
onto a heated plate.

10:37.150 --> 10:39.084
[Fish Hits Floor]

10:43.990 --> 10:48.324
There's one thing that's
paramount for every cook to keep
in the back of their mind.

10:54.867 --> 10:57.097
Only you know
what goes on in the kitchen.

10:57.170 --> 11:00.606
Join me next week:
Hannah's Country Kitchen Cooking.

11:02.809 --> 11:04.743
And we're clear.
[Chuckles]

11:04.811 --> 11:09.305
Hannah, that was incredible!
I smell a fourth Emmy.

11:13.119 --> 11:15.485
I don't wanna see any more
of these. Hmm?

11:15.555 --> 11:17.819
Tough. Oh, l--

11:17.890 --> 11:21.291
Mmm. It's delicious.
What?

11:21.361 --> 11:23.761
[Chuckles]
Nothing.

11:28.935 --> 11:31.426
You can never stop, can you?

11:31.504 --> 11:35.167
- Stop what?
- Organizing things.

11:35.241 --> 11:38.699
- Oh, I'll stop if it bothers you.
- No.

11:38.778 --> 11:41.770
It doesn't bother me.
It takes me back.

11:44.951 --> 11:47.215
Sit next to me.

11:58.564 --> 12:00.998
It's a hell of a way
for you to find out, huh?

12:01.067 --> 12:04.161
- Find out what?
- Well, that I'm gay, for one.

12:06.039 --> 12:08.530
Come on.
You never suspected?

12:08.608 --> 12:12.510
- You were always so good at sports.
- [Chuckles] Mom!

12:12.578 --> 12:17.038
I'm really glad you're here.

12:18.551 --> 12:21.850
- And what's the second thing?
- What second thing?

12:21.921 --> 12:26.187
You said it was a hell of a way
for me to find out that you
were gay for "one" thing.

12:26.259 --> 12:28.693
- So what's the second thing?
- That I'm dying.

12:28.761 --> 12:32.561
- Don't say that!
- Oh, stop! I can't go back into
our classic mother-son pattern.

12:32.632 --> 12:37.729
Okay? I can't play the Iverson family
game of denying reality...

12:37.804 --> 12:40.398
- where reality is over there,
somewhere...
- Oh, honey, don't.

12:40.473 --> 12:43.772
and we hide from it over here
and pretend it doesn't exist.

12:43.843 --> 12:47.677
Okay? It takes too much energy.
Energy that I don't have.

12:47.747 --> 12:49.942
All right. Maybe I don't either...
have the energy.

12:50.016 --> 12:52.007
God, that would be good.

12:52.085 --> 12:54.553
All right, we'll start fresh.

12:54.620 --> 12:56.554
Pattern-free.

12:56.622 --> 13:00.786
Within these four walls,
reality will prevail.

13:00.860 --> 13:04.159
And if I slip up,
you-- you let me know.

13:04.230 --> 13:06.130
You'll--
You'll be the first.

13:10.236 --> 13:13.535
They say first steps
are the hardest.

13:19.579 --> 13:22.639
The doctor said
you haven't had any visitors.

13:22.715 --> 13:27.516
You know me, Mom. I've never been
one to have a lot of friends.

13:27.587 --> 13:31.580
Besides, I seem to be
the last of my small crowd.

13:31.657 --> 13:33.716
What about your roommate Jack?

13:36.062 --> 13:40.260
He wasn't my roommate, Mother,
and he died a year ago.

13:45.138 --> 13:47.106
Hey, how's the commercial going?

13:47.173 --> 13:49.107
It's on hold for a week.

13:49.175 --> 13:53.737
The geniuses at Pacific Motors
have now decided to spotlight the car...

13:53.813 --> 13:55.747
and dumb down the concept.

13:55.815 --> 14:00.479
- No Fellini?
- Who? Most definitely no Fellini.

14:00.553 --> 14:03.215
But my play's not falling apart.

14:03.289 --> 14:05.314
- I'm happy for you.
- Thank you.

14:05.391 --> 14:07.484
Bosco, where do you keep
Theater Week?

14:07.560 --> 14:11.587
Top shelf. Between Psychology Today
and Martha Stewart Living.

14:14.300 --> 14:16.234
Uh-oh!
Whoa!

14:16.302 --> 14:19.396
Jesus! Meredith?

14:19.472 --> 14:22.464
Jimmy, grab that side! Grab that side.
Okay. Everyone. All right, fellas.

14:22.542 --> 14:26.137
On three. One--
Oh. Okay. All right.

14:26.212 --> 14:28.874
- Can we say "lawsuit"?
- Uh, are you okay?

14:28.948 --> 14:31.974
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Fine.
I landed on a stack of George.

14:32.051 --> 14:35.145
- Plenty of padding.
- Meet the architect.

14:35.221 --> 14:39.351
- Are you sure you're okay?
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine. Thank you.

14:39.425 --> 14:42.917
- If I can just find one,
Theater Week is on me.
- And dinner is on me.

14:42.995 --> 14:46.954
- No, no. Not necessary. Truly.
- Please. I insist.
It's the least I can do. I mean--

14:47.033 --> 14:50.400
- Look, I'm not gonna sue you, okay?
- I didn't think you were gonna sue me.

14:52.872 --> 14:55.636
Not that I couldn't, mind you.
But something tells me...

14:55.708 --> 14:58.973
that you'd be able to convince
the jury that this was my fault.

14:59.045 --> 15:03.846
You know I'm not just asking you
to dinner as a preemptive strike
against litigation.

15:03.916 --> 15:06.407
- I'm asking because--
- I'll have dinner with you.

15:08.087 --> 15:11.318
- What changed your mind?
- Anybody who can say
"preemptive strike...

15:11.390 --> 15:14.484
against litigation" with a straight face
deserves a dinner companion.

15:14.560 --> 15:17.393
- [Chuckles]
- Thank you.

15:18.598 --> 15:20.088
This is last week's.

15:20.233 --> 15:23.930
I'm thinking of putting
the show on hiatus.

15:24.003 --> 15:26.597
And I'm thinking
you'll do no such thing.

15:26.672 --> 15:32.008
- But, Paul--
- No. I don't want anything
to be any different.

15:32.078 --> 15:35.809
- Things are different.
- I don't want to have a fight with you.

15:35.881 --> 15:39.078
I don't want a fight. I just--
I just want to talk and make--

15:39.151 --> 15:43.485
Look. What about what I want?
You've always controlled everything:

15:43.556 --> 15:45.547
your shows, the kids.

15:45.625 --> 15:48.355
Stop trying to control me.

15:48.427 --> 15:50.418
I'm not trying
to control anybody.

15:50.496 --> 15:53.294
- I just think maybe--
- Don't think.

15:53.366 --> 15:57.166
Let us just proceed as if
nothing has changed. All right?

16:01.374 --> 16:05.435
- I don't know if I can do that.
- You have no choice.

16:07.346 --> 16:10.611
I may have just enough time left
to become an alcoholic.

16:13.819 --> 16:17.255
% [Techno]

16:17.323 --> 16:32.262
%

16:44.450 --> 16:48.045
I don't care who had her first. I poke
around her stool looking for worms.

16:48.120 --> 16:50.179
I feed the fucking thing.
I take her to the vet.

16:50.256 --> 16:52.383
All you do is pet her twice a day.

16:52.458 --> 16:55.359
Which is a hell of a lot more
than you've been doing to me lately.

16:55.428 --> 16:57.589
Okay, let's discuss this calmly.

16:57.663 --> 17:01.429
We're adults.
We've been together a long time.

17:01.500 --> 17:03.866
Well, not a long time,
but an adequate four months.

17:03.936 --> 17:07.804
Adequate until you fuckin' cheated on me
with that skag from Bloomingdale's!

17:07.873 --> 17:09.807
You fu--
Harry?

17:09.875 --> 17:13.538
Don't you dare hang up.
Harry! Harry?

17:14.814 --> 17:17.305
Shit! Shit.

17:24.656 --> 17:27.251
Hi. You got a quarter?

17:31.864 --> 17:33.798
Thank you.

17:39.271 --> 17:41.205
The fucking cat is mine.

17:42.375 --> 17:45.173
No, no.
On this I'm not negotiable, Harry.

17:45.244 --> 17:48.179
Harry. Hey! Hey!
Don't be a fuckin' infant, okay?

17:48.247 --> 17:52.206
You can take anything that came
from IKEA. I want the cat,
and I want Pottery Barn.

17:52.284 --> 17:54.718
It--
One more time.

17:54.787 --> 17:57.688
You hang up one more time and l--
[Slams Down Receiver]

17:57.757 --> 17:59.691
Damn it.

18:03.295 --> 18:05.923
- It's my last one.
- Negotiations are almost over.

18:07.967 --> 18:09.901
Thank you.

18:14.140 --> 18:17.473
All right. Okay, scumbag.
You're robbing me blind...

18:17.543 --> 18:21.343
but I will give up Pottery Barn
if I can just have the cat.

18:22.848 --> 18:26.215
No! No. Pottery Barn does not
include Williams Sonoma.

18:26.285 --> 18:29.482
They're two separate
establishments, Harry.

18:29.555 --> 18:31.989
Oh, Christ on crutches!
Okay, you know what, Harry?

18:32.057 --> 18:36.016
I want to get rid of you as much as l
want to get rid of that junk from IKEA.

18:36.095 --> 18:38.529
So here's the thing.

18:38.597 --> 18:42.590
You can walk away with Pottery Barn,
Williams Sonoma, IKEA.

18:42.668 --> 18:47.537
And just to show you that I'm
a grown-up, I will throw in all
the crap from Hold Everything!

18:47.606 --> 18:50.404
Yeah! Yeah, that includes
the hanging shoe sorter.

18:50.476 --> 18:54.344
That's right.
Do we have a deal? Great.

18:54.413 --> 18:57.507
So here's the thing.
I will be home in two hours.

18:57.583 --> 19:00.916
You and all your junk
from the catalogs will be gone...

19:00.986 --> 19:03.614
and the cat will be there waiting
for me, purring contentedly.

19:07.626 --> 19:11.756
Well, the least I can do
after taking your last quarter
is let you buy me a drink.

19:24.610 --> 19:27.636
I work in the Twin Towers.
Entertainment law.

19:29.748 --> 19:32.148
- And you?
- Me?

19:32.218 --> 19:34.345
I'm not very good company.
I'm-- I'm sorry.

19:36.722 --> 19:38.656
No problem.

19:42.194 --> 19:45.322
- I'm not gonna bother you.
- Uh, don't go. l-l-I'm sorry.

19:45.397 --> 19:48.332
- No, I'm sorry. Really.
- Again, I'm sorry.

19:50.603 --> 19:53.902
- You've had a bad day.
- A killer.

19:53.973 --> 19:58.239
You know, yesterday I would have
said that things couldn't
possibly get any worse.

19:58.310 --> 20:00.744
They sure as hell
got worse today.

20:02.314 --> 20:06.148
I'm, uh--
I work in the, uh, Twin Towers too.

20:06.218 --> 20:09.710
I'm a development executive
over at ABC.

20:09.788 --> 20:13.554
I'm responsible for all those shit shows
that you don't watch on Thursday night.

20:13.626 --> 20:15.992
You're to blame for those?

20:16.061 --> 20:18.427
- Afraid so.
- [Laughs]

20:18.497 --> 20:20.431
Everybody blames me.

20:20.499 --> 20:24.458
My boss, my wife, my secretary.

20:24.537 --> 20:26.471
Hell, even my kids.
They watch NBC.

20:26.539 --> 20:30.270
And I work like a dog...

20:30.342 --> 20:34.039
trying to find some way to fix
the Thursday night schedule.

20:37.950 --> 20:40.680
Well, I don't find a way to fix
the Thursday night schedule...

20:40.753 --> 20:42.880
and my boss,
today he tells me...

20:42.955 --> 20:46.857
that coming into the office
tomorrow isn't necessary.

20:46.926 --> 20:51.659
Or coming in ever again,
for that matter.

20:53.499 --> 20:56.991
[Sighs] I wish you could
spend the night.

20:57.069 --> 20:59.003
You know I can't.

21:00.439 --> 21:02.566
- Is this all you want from us?
- Roger...

21:02.641 --> 21:06.168
and I mean this really sweetly,
there isn't any us.

21:06.245 --> 21:10.045
- Mmm. There's only this.
- Well, this could be different.

21:10.115 --> 21:12.242
Well, anything
can be different.

21:12.318 --> 21:14.479
But I don't want this to be.

21:14.553 --> 21:19.422
I want it to be what it is:
two very sexually compatible
people enjoying each other...

21:19.491 --> 21:22.892
with no obligations,
no complications...

21:22.962 --> 21:25.260
no individual history,
no mutual history...

21:25.331 --> 21:27.765
[Slaps Roger]
and no guilt.

21:27.833 --> 21:30.324
- That's awfully cold.
- It's awfully realistic.

21:30.402 --> 21:33.428
- I know you don't love your husband.
- Oh, but I know...

21:33.505 --> 21:36.133
that you do love your wife.

21:41.046 --> 21:43.480
I'll have a vodka martini,
very dry and straight up...

21:43.549 --> 21:48.577
- with three olives,
and my sullen friend here will have--
- A Coke.

21:48.654 --> 21:52.283
The poster boy for designated drivers
will have a Coke.

21:54.560 --> 21:57.222
- The guy on the phone?
- Harry.

21:57.296 --> 21:59.787
Harry, right.
We were together for five months.

21:59.865 --> 22:02.425
- I thought it was four.
- You were paying attention.

22:02.501 --> 22:04.765
Everyone in this club
was paying attention.

22:04.837 --> 22:07.271
We were together for five months.
But I knew it wasn't gonna work out...

22:07.339 --> 22:10.900
'cause the first time he comes over
I find out that he sits down to pee.

22:10.976 --> 22:14.434
- You don't do that, do you?
- No.

22:14.513 --> 22:16.481
So fuckin' lazy.
And in my experience...

22:16.548 --> 22:20.177
it extends to other aspects
of an individual's personality.

22:20.252 --> 22:25.087
Last time I saw him, Harry was wearing a
blue sweater and an idiotic expression.

22:25.157 --> 22:27.557
The sweater was new.

22:27.626 --> 22:29.787
Here's to good riddance Harry.

22:30.863 --> 22:32.797
Good riddance Harry.

22:42.107 --> 22:44.974
Hey, again please.

22:45.044 --> 22:48.207
And drier this time,
and three olives, not two.

22:48.280 --> 22:50.714
Three.
Nutritional value.

22:50.783 --> 22:52.774
Now, where were we?
Oh, so Harry.

22:52.851 --> 22:55.183
Right.

22:55.254 --> 22:57.313
The sex part wasn't bad.

22:57.389 --> 22:59.323
You know, for a while.

22:59.391 --> 23:04.488
And then his consummate laziness
and lack of imagination
became tediously self-evident.

23:04.563 --> 23:09.557
Every time, everything was
exactly the same as the time previous.

23:09.635 --> 23:13.935
It was as if he had followed
some step-by-step instructional video.

23:14.006 --> 23:17.498
And about two weeks ago,
guess what I found in the apartment.

23:17.576 --> 23:22.570
- A step-by-step instructional video.
- Right! Here's the topper.

23:22.648 --> 23:25.708
I timed his performance
one night. Right?

23:25.784 --> 23:29.151
And then I checked the running time
on the video. And guess what.

23:29.221 --> 23:31.815
- To the minute.
- Right down to it.

23:31.890 --> 23:33.824
Twenty-three minutes, to be exact.

23:33.892 --> 23:35.826
Including credits.

23:36.895 --> 23:40.456
Anyway, he's history.

23:40.532 --> 23:43.626
- But I still have Blanche.
- Who would be the cat.

23:43.702 --> 23:46.193
Oh, a great cat.
Very feline.

23:46.271 --> 23:48.364
The best cats are.

23:48.440 --> 23:52.001
Blanche can look at you with a gaze
of unflappable superiority...

23:52.077 --> 23:56.480
that seems to spring from near total
detachment and disinterest.

23:57.916 --> 24:00.680
Not unlike
how you're looking at me now.

24:04.890 --> 24:06.824
Thank you.

24:08.761 --> 24:11.491
You don't say very much, do you?

24:11.563 --> 24:15.499
- Does anyone, when they're with you?
- Don't get mean.

24:17.536 --> 24:21.597
We don't know each other well enough
yet. When we do, then you can get mean.

24:24.510 --> 24:26.774
So we should do this again sometime.

24:26.845 --> 24:30.303
- We're not doing anything.
- Okay. Then let's not do this.

24:30.382 --> 24:33.010
Let's do something else.

24:33.085 --> 24:35.383
I'll even let you be the man.
You can decide where we go on our date.

24:37.623 --> 24:40.456
I don't date.

24:40.526 --> 24:44.292
Well. Gee, I don't have
a witty comeback for that one.

24:44.363 --> 24:46.627
I mean, I'm used to
any number of brush-offs...

24:46.698 --> 24:49.166
but that's, uh, that's a new one.

24:49.234 --> 24:52.203
Doesn't date.

24:52.271 --> 24:55.729
I'll admit I've seen you around. You're
always-- You're always dancing alone.

24:57.576 --> 25:00.409
- That's the way I like it.
- Why is that?

25:02.781 --> 25:05.011
I don't want to be
rude or unkind...

25:05.083 --> 25:07.517
or... mean.

25:09.788 --> 25:13.087
But I just don't come out with my entire
life story over martinis and a Coke.

25:16.829 --> 25:19.229
I'm sorry, really.

25:19.298 --> 25:21.823
Your cat's lucky to have you.

25:29.908 --> 25:33.344
My wife had moved them out.

25:33.412 --> 25:36.210
Moved everything out.
Left a note.

25:36.281 --> 25:38.613
Very thoughtful.
Didn't realize she felt that way.

25:38.684 --> 25:40.515
What way?

25:44.323 --> 25:46.791
That I was a failure.

25:46.859 --> 25:50.659
Not only professionally,
but personally as well.

25:50.729 --> 25:54.563
Just like ABC no longer required
my services. She let me know...

25:54.633 --> 26:00.071
that she and the kids no longer
required my services or my presence.

26:00.138 --> 26:04.234
It turns out she's been
seeing some guy for a year...

26:04.309 --> 26:07.437
for a fucking year,
and I never suspected a thing.

26:07.512 --> 26:09.810
- And you know what the worst of it is?
- What?

26:09.882 --> 26:12.680
The guy that she left me for?
The fucker works for NBC!

26:12.751 --> 26:16.187
He's got my wife and my kids,
my cat and my dog...

26:16.255 --> 26:20.021
and he doesn't have to lose
any sleep over the Thursday
night fucking schedule!

26:28.400 --> 26:30.630
Honey?

26:30.702 --> 26:34.570
You should come to bed.
What are you working on so late?

26:34.640 --> 26:36.972
I was just checking on
your TV residuals.

26:37.042 --> 26:39.442
They're still robbing us blind.

26:39.511 --> 26:42.605
I happen to know you're
a tremendous hit on WWFU.

26:42.681 --> 26:44.376
Which is where?

26:44.449 --> 26:46.610
Intercourse, Pennsylvania.

26:46.685 --> 26:49.210
Oh, Intercourse.

26:49.288 --> 26:51.756
And they can't get enough
of you in Intercourse.

26:51.823 --> 26:53.757
And I know exactly
how they feel.

26:55.694 --> 26:58.424
- Bed.
- [Imitates Dog Panting]

26:59.865 --> 27:02.595
- Come on, Molly. Come on, Crackers.
- [Dog Whimpers]

27:11.143 --> 27:14.169
[Waiter]
There you are, sir. Okay?

27:14.246 --> 27:18.478
- Cheers.
- I've been meaning to ask you
about your wedding ring.

27:21.053 --> 27:24.955
It's really just force
of habit. l, uh...

27:25.023 --> 27:29.255
divorced...
four chilling years ago.

27:30.329 --> 27:33.059
- Acrimonious?
- No.

27:33.131 --> 27:36.328
Oh, wait, that means
hostile and bitter. Yes.

27:36.401 --> 27:40.269
In the divorce papers she referred to me
as the "architect of her misfortune."

27:41.373 --> 27:45.002
- Ouch.
- Yeah. No kids, luckily.

27:45.077 --> 27:49.673
I wanted them,
but she didn't.

27:49.748 --> 27:51.682
- You know, if this makes you
uncomfortable--
- No.

27:51.750 --> 27:54.082
- I can take it off, the ring.
It's not a problem.
- No, no. Stop.

27:54.152 --> 27:58.612
Don't be silly.
That would be two of us being silly.

27:58.690 --> 28:02.717
I really only wear it to keep
the construction guys from harassing me.

28:03.996 --> 28:06.692
- Does it work?
- [Chuckles]

28:06.765 --> 28:09.825
Depends on what I'm wearing.
[Chuckles]

28:12.371 --> 28:16.432
[Sighs] I think you can tell
that I'm not very good at this.

28:19.111 --> 28:22.342
- You're charming.
- [Laughs]

28:23.582 --> 28:27.313
- And real.
- [Laughing]

28:27.386 --> 28:29.854
Lovely.

28:29.921 --> 28:32.219
What did I say?

28:32.290 --> 28:34.349
Nothing.

28:34.426 --> 28:36.417
No, no. Nothing.

28:36.495 --> 28:39.589
I just, um--

28:39.664 --> 28:44.795
Before I came here tonight,
I was discussing you with my sister.

28:44.870 --> 28:48.362
We were coming up with
a psychological profile.

28:48.440 --> 28:50.374
Several, actually.

28:50.442 --> 28:54.310
- And which did I fit into?
- Oh, none.

28:54.379 --> 28:57.576
I think I'm gonna have to
revise the filing system.

28:57.649 --> 29:01.608
Put you in
the "too good to be true" category.

29:01.686 --> 29:05.622
Mmm.
But not to worry.

29:05.690 --> 29:08.523
I just know you'll turn out
to be involved with somebody else...

29:08.593 --> 29:12.120
or... gay or crazy.

29:13.432 --> 29:16.333
[Sighs]

29:16.401 --> 29:19.370
Well, it's a definite possibility.

29:22.140 --> 29:24.074
Crazy, huh?

29:25.243 --> 29:27.177
Certifiable.

29:27.245 --> 29:29.179
- [Sighs]
- [TV, Indistinct]

29:31.049 --> 29:32.983
Mom.

29:34.419 --> 29:36.979
I know you've spoken to my doctor.

29:37.055 --> 29:40.183
I know. I know he told you
I don't have long...

29:40.258 --> 29:42.726
so let's not pretend
that I do, okay?

29:44.863 --> 29:46.797
Want to watch another movie?

29:46.865 --> 29:49.425
No. God, no.

29:51.403 --> 29:54.861
I tell you what I would like,
is I'd like to play a game.

29:54.940 --> 30:00.071
- Should I get a deck of cards?
- No. Not that kind of game.

30:00.145 --> 30:03.979
- What?
- I want each of us to take some time...

30:04.049 --> 30:08.247
and think of something that we have
always wanted to tell the other.

30:09.321 --> 30:12.017
Something private, some secret...

30:12.090 --> 30:14.490
some feeling or memory.

30:14.559 --> 30:18.120
It could be anything.
Just as long as it's truthful.

30:18.196 --> 30:21.495
Uh, I don't know
if I'd be good at that kind of game.

30:21.566 --> 30:23.466
Will you try for me?

30:27.139 --> 30:29.937
[Sighs]

30:30.008 --> 30:31.942
Um--

30:43.155 --> 30:45.487
I'm waiting.

30:48.126 --> 30:50.594
I never loved your father.

30:50.662 --> 30:52.596
Not for a minute.

30:53.965 --> 30:57.264
Wow. You're good at this.

31:01.173 --> 31:04.267
- Why did you marry him?
- Oh.

31:04.342 --> 31:06.367
I was pushing 30.

31:06.444 --> 31:10.312
Back then we called that
a last chance for happiness.

31:10.382 --> 31:13.874
He had a good business.
I remember my mother saying, "Marry him.

31:13.952 --> 31:16.045
He's an undertaker
and will never be out of work.

31:16.121 --> 31:18.021
People will always--"

31:20.025 --> 31:21.959
People will always die.

31:25.697 --> 31:27.631
People will always die.

31:35.874 --> 31:38.934
I hope it's okay for me
to say this, but...

31:39.010 --> 31:42.377
you strike me
as someone who's been...

31:42.447 --> 31:44.847
burned romantically.

31:46.484 --> 31:48.611
Scalded.

31:48.687 --> 31:51.383
Repeatedly.

31:51.456 --> 31:54.687
- Married?
- [Sighs]

31:54.759 --> 31:58.024
- Divorced?
- Yes.

31:58.096 --> 32:00.223
But that was a long time ago...

32:00.298 --> 32:02.562
and, believe it or not,
one of my better experiences.

32:02.634 --> 32:04.568
[Chuckles]
Let me guess.

32:04.636 --> 32:07.799
Uh, he was either involved
with somebody else...

32:07.872 --> 32:09.999
or gay...

32:10.075 --> 32:12.009
or crazy.

32:12.077 --> 32:14.011
Actually, yes.

32:15.747 --> 32:18.409
Involved with someone else?

32:18.483 --> 32:22.214
- Crazy?
- No. He was gay.

32:22.287 --> 32:24.551
- Wow. Really?
- Yeah.

32:24.623 --> 32:27.353
- I mean, I'm sorry.
- No.

32:27.425 --> 32:29.620
- I mean, I'm not sorry. I mean, uh--
- [Laughs]

32:31.029 --> 32:34.021
- Save me.
- It's okay.

32:34.099 --> 32:36.659
He was a great guy.

32:36.735 --> 32:40.694
I married the boy next door.
Literally. We were 19.

32:40.772 --> 32:43.741
It didn't last very long.
Couldn't, of course.

32:45.443 --> 32:49.174
I haven't seen him in a long time,
but, uh, but we're still friends.

32:49.247 --> 32:53.547
Which is more than I can say for the
parade of total losers that followed.

32:53.618 --> 32:58.214
Are there any, uh,
recent or current losers?

32:58.290 --> 33:00.281
No.

33:00.358 --> 33:04.385
I've been in a holding pattern
where romance is concerned.

33:04.462 --> 33:07.989
- Well, things can change quickly.
- Yeah.

33:12.570 --> 33:15.664
I'm sorry.

33:15.740 --> 33:19.801
This is, uh, going
a little too quickly for me.

33:21.746 --> 33:23.680
I can go slow.

33:24.849 --> 33:26.783
Look, Trent,
you're a nice guy. l--

33:26.851 --> 33:30.947
- Aw! Aw. That's-- You know?
- What?

33:31.022 --> 33:33.456
- I'm swimming ashore.
You can call the Coast Guard.
- Oh, come on.

33:33.525 --> 33:35.925
"Nice guy"? That's--

33:35.994 --> 33:40.363
I haven't been dismissed
with that since high school.

33:40.432 --> 33:42.923
Does that mean no second date?

33:43.001 --> 33:45.333
I have a hard time trusting men.

33:45.403 --> 33:49.237
I'm not men.
I'm not a group. Just me.

33:50.475 --> 33:52.875
Who probably has
a lot of women after him.

33:52.944 --> 33:56.141
- So?
- So--

33:56.214 --> 33:58.808
Look, you know,
you seem to want honesty...

33:58.883 --> 34:00.817
so I'll be honest with you.

34:00.885 --> 34:03.046
I don't really have
a problem getting dates.

34:03.121 --> 34:06.648
But I'm 38 years old.
I don't just want dates anymore.

34:06.725 --> 34:09.193
I'll tell you what I don't want.

34:09.260 --> 34:12.627
I don't want all of
this calculated artificiality.

34:12.697 --> 34:17.793
This isn't me, Trent--
this dress, the stupid little bows
in my hair. And look at you.

34:17.869 --> 34:21.862
I mean, I don't imagine you sit around
your house in an Armani suit. Do you?

34:21.940 --> 34:25.341
No. My house is black-tie.

34:25.409 --> 34:27.344
[Giggles]

34:31.815 --> 34:34.341
- Look, I'm sorry, but--
- I know, you have to go.

34:34.418 --> 34:37.786
- I'm already-- Jesus-- two hours late.
- You're leavin' me too.

34:37.856 --> 34:40.654
It's okay. Really.
Just go. Go.

34:40.725 --> 34:44.889
- Until the day I die,
I'll remember that story.
- Yeah, listen. Listen.

34:44.963 --> 34:49.059
You have been swell,
listening to me like this.

34:49.134 --> 34:53.661
Bet you'll think twice about striking up
a conversation in this bar again, huh?

34:53.737 --> 34:56.103
[Chuckles]
Take care. All right?

34:56.174 --> 34:58.642
- For once I really, really mean that.
- Yeah.

34:58.710 --> 35:01.076
- Good-bye.
- Bye.

35:06.885 --> 35:08.819
Taxi money.

35:08.887 --> 35:11.355
Don't even think of allowing
that guy to drive.

35:11.423 --> 35:14.119
I'm a lawyer.
I'll hunt you down.

35:20.665 --> 35:22.963
Look, Trent...

35:23.034 --> 35:26.333
if by some miracle,
after this explosion of neuroses...

35:26.404 --> 35:28.804
you still want to see me,
we can start from the top.

35:28.873 --> 35:31.307
You can cook dinner
for me Tuesday.

35:32.544 --> 35:34.978
- Okay.
- Good.

35:36.181 --> 35:38.615
- Tuesday.
- Yeah.

35:38.683 --> 35:41.846
- You can come to my apartment.
- Okay.

35:41.920 --> 35:45.083
Meet my better half.

35:45.156 --> 35:49.559
- Better half?
- Yeah. My dog. Barley.

35:49.627 --> 35:52.357
Your dog Barley? That'd be great.
I'd love to meet Barley.

35:52.430 --> 35:54.364
- Good.
- I'll bring the wine.

35:54.432 --> 35:56.559
- Great.
- Good.

35:56.634 --> 35:59.228
- Tuesday night.
- Absolutely.

35:59.304 --> 36:03.070
You know, Meredith,
those stupid little bows?

36:04.142 --> 36:06.076
I think they're adorable.

37:21.986 --> 37:23.920
[Sighs]

37:23.988 --> 37:26.957
Why did you stay with him?

37:27.025 --> 37:30.290
Well, you.

37:30.361 --> 37:34.525
I guess I was the last generation
of women who actually did that.

37:34.599 --> 37:38.365
It never even occurred to me
to get a divorce.

37:38.436 --> 37:42.463
[Sighs]
I was so relieved when he died.

37:42.540 --> 37:47.876
- Don't hold anything back, Mom.
- [Chuckles] Mmm.

37:47.946 --> 37:51.905
Ah, I like this
new spirit of frankness.

37:51.983 --> 37:54.543
It's oddly cleansing.

38:05.396 --> 38:08.058
I want to know
what you're like away from me here.

38:08.132 --> 38:12.296
That can't happen. The fact that you and
I aren't involved beyond this room...

38:12.370 --> 38:14.702
is what-- ahh-- appeals to me.

38:14.772 --> 38:18.765
You know how to play
your role damn well.

38:18.843 --> 38:21.539
[Laughs]
Guilty as charged.

38:24.449 --> 38:26.383
[Moans]

38:30.288 --> 38:34.554
- Roger, what do you want?
- I don't want much.

38:34.626 --> 38:37.754
I just want more of you.

38:39.797 --> 38:41.731
I can't give you that.

38:44.335 --> 38:47.964
Roger.
Don't be an anger ball.

38:48.039 --> 38:49.973
"An anger ball"?

38:51.576 --> 38:54.977
Don't you see?
What's great about you and me...

38:55.046 --> 38:59.881
right here, this very moment,
is that we don't come through
that door with a lot of baggage.

38:59.951 --> 39:03.717
We don't come through that door
with any baggage at all.

39:03.788 --> 39:07.747
And aren't we lucky?
We don't bring anything in...

39:07.825 --> 39:11.124
and we don't take anything out.

39:13.631 --> 39:16.862
% [Techno, Loud]

39:16.934 --> 39:26.707
%

39:26.778 --> 39:29.474
You're not the only one
who can dance alone.

39:29.547 --> 39:33.483
- What?
- I said you look like
a man in need of a Coke.

39:37.655 --> 39:40.351
%

39:40.425 --> 39:43.121
[Laughing]

39:43.194 --> 39:46.493
Uh, my friend here will have a Coke,
and I'll have a--

39:46.564 --> 39:50.261
Vodka martini,
very dry, three olives.

39:50.334 --> 39:52.268
Good memory.

39:52.336 --> 39:55.499
My mind has an endless capacity
for useless information.

39:58.009 --> 40:00.671
I've had a terrible day.

40:00.745 --> 40:04.112
I know we were talking about you for
a moment there, but my day was so bad.

40:04.182 --> 40:06.650
"How bad was it?" you might ask.

40:06.718 --> 40:09.744
-l might if you gave me the opportunity.
-l was saving you the effort...

40:09.821 --> 40:12.756
so that after I tell you my tale of woe
we can move on to happier topics.

40:12.824 --> 40:16.590
Perhaps one of your choosing. Anyway,
I'm an actress. Did I tell you that?

40:16.661 --> 40:21.030
- No. But I'm not surprised.
- I had this monologue in class today.

40:21.099 --> 40:24.762
And I was prepared.
You know, I mean, like really prepared.

40:24.836 --> 40:27.168
You know Suddenly Last Summer
by Tennessee Williams?

40:27.238 --> 40:30.867
- No.
- Oh, it's one of my favorites.
Great story.

40:30.942 --> 40:33.638
It's about this girl, Katherine-- moi--

40:33.711 --> 40:37.442
who is slated for a lobotomy
because the mother of her cousin
wants to keep her mouth shut...

40:37.515 --> 40:40.916
about certain goings-on involving
the old lady's son Sebastian.

40:40.985 --> 40:45.115
You see, the women sort of pimp
for Cousin Sebastian.
Are you following this?

40:45.189 --> 40:46.986
- Amazingly, yes.
- Anyway, it turns out...

40:47.058 --> 40:51.154
on their travels together Cousin
Sebastian liked to troll the beaches...

40:51.229 --> 40:55.689
looking for young native boys
in order to satisfy his base instincts.

40:55.767 --> 40:58.497
One hot afternoon in Cartagena...

40:58.569 --> 41:02.232
the boys decide they have had quite
enough of Sebastian's shenanigans...

41:02.306 --> 41:05.742
and they--
well, they eat him.

41:05.810 --> 41:09.337
- You mean metaphorically.
- No. They really eat him.

41:09.413 --> 41:14.077
They devour him.
In short, he's lunch.

41:14.152 --> 41:17.019
And Katherine witnesses
every course...

41:17.088 --> 41:19.420
from soup to nuts.

41:19.490 --> 41:21.720
If you'll pardon the expression.

41:21.793 --> 41:25.320
Anyway, I'm about to do
this killer monologue. I'm up next--

41:25.396 --> 41:28.957
If one more actor saunters
into this class...

41:29.033 --> 41:33.834
and recites Katherine's "native boys
ate my cousin Sebastian" speech...

41:33.905 --> 41:36.100
from Suddenly Last Summer...

41:36.174 --> 41:39.041
I am going to puke.

41:39.110 --> 41:42.477
Now, who is up next?

41:43.815 --> 41:47.808
- Um... Joan! You're on.
- [Moans]

41:49.287 --> 41:52.950
The teacher didn't lose
his lunch. I did.

41:54.025 --> 41:56.789
- I'm sorry.
- So am l.

41:59.664 --> 42:03.828
Now, on to happier topics, I promise.
How about a movie?

42:03.901 --> 42:05.732
- I told you.
- I know.

42:05.803 --> 42:08.636
I know. You don't date.
Is it a religious thing?

42:08.706 --> 42:12.767
- No.
- Well, you like movies, don't you?

42:12.844 --> 42:14.778
- They're okay.
- How about tomorrow night?

42:14.846 --> 42:17.644
It doesn't have to be a date.
We'll meet at the theater.

42:19.350 --> 42:22.979
- I don't know.
- Look. I'll make it easy.
Okay, blue boy?

42:23.054 --> 42:26.888
Tomorrow night I'm going to the
late show of the Texas Chainsaw Massacre
at the Sunset Five.

42:26.958 --> 42:29.893
If you decide you would like to
join the human race, meet me there.

42:35.366 --> 42:39.700
Uh, now, in other news, they found
a cure for cancer. Okay. Uh, moving on.

42:39.770 --> 42:42.898
-No, they--
-[Hannah] Do you ever hear from Wendy?

42:42.974 --> 42:46.569
- [TV Volume Decreases]
- What on Earth made you think of Wendy?

42:46.644 --> 42:51.240
- Oh, I don't know.
Just thinking about the old days.
- Yes.

42:51.315 --> 42:53.715
Very old. Ancient.

42:55.353 --> 43:00.154
Well, do you?
Do you ever hear from her?

43:00.224 --> 43:02.158
Any reason I should?

43:02.226 --> 43:05.753
Any reason you should keep
her picture in your desk?

43:08.633 --> 43:12.865
- [TV Volume Increases]
- None that you should
concern yourself with.

43:12.937 --> 43:17.567
[Bill Maher]
Viagra. Oh, God.

43:17.642 --> 43:21.510
Viagra. That's what everyone's
talking about. Are you on it yet?

43:21.579 --> 43:23.740
Just the men.
Okay, uh, well...

43:23.814 --> 43:26.044
it's so successful,
you know, of course--

43:36.427 --> 43:38.361
- Hey. I made it.
- Hi.

43:38.429 --> 43:42.559
- Uh, casually attired.
- Wow.

43:42.633 --> 43:45.067
Yeah, I know. The flowers are
a little much, and I'm late.

43:45.136 --> 43:47.263
But only because I had second thoughts
about the flowers...

43:47.338 --> 43:50.364
and I threw them away halfway down the
block, and then I had third thoughts...

43:50.441 --> 43:52.466
and went back and got them.

43:52.543 --> 43:54.807
Well, I'm glad you did.

43:54.879 --> 43:57.177
Thank you.

43:57.248 --> 43:59.182
Come in.
Come in, come in, come in.

43:59.250 --> 44:03.380
- Thanks.
- l, uh-- I hope you like Italian.

44:03.454 --> 44:05.649
- I hope you like merlot.
- I do.

44:05.723 --> 44:07.748
- [Dog Panting]
- Wow! That's a--

44:07.825 --> 44:09.759
- Barley.
- That's some dog! That's, uh--

44:09.827 --> 44:13.058
- Barley, get down, sweetie.
Come on. Come on.
- Whoa.

44:13.130 --> 44:15.758
- My family has a thing for pets.
- Yeah. Oh.

44:15.833 --> 44:18.301
That's, uh--
That's certainly impressive.

44:18.369 --> 44:22.897
Suddenly I'm feeling
a little inadequate. That's--

44:23.975 --> 44:26.603
I, uh-- It's almost ready.
I, uh--

44:26.677 --> 44:31.341
Sorry that took me so long. I was
on the phone with one of my sisters.

44:32.650 --> 44:36.177
- The married one.
- The one who's having an affair?

44:36.253 --> 44:38.483
Yeah, well, the one
who's always having an affair.

44:38.556 --> 44:40.820
Her husband doesn't
suspect anything?

44:40.891 --> 44:44.520
Her husband is sweet,
but he's a bit dim.

44:46.063 --> 44:48.657
He doesn't have
much of an imagination.

44:48.733 --> 44:51.668
Chandler girls like their men
with imagination?

44:51.736 --> 44:54.034
Yeah. It helps.

44:55.373 --> 44:59.639
You know, I'm told
I have a good imagination.

45:01.645 --> 45:03.840
I don't want
to have sex tonight.

45:07.551 --> 45:10.884
- Okay.
- I mean if that's why you thought
I invited you over here--

45:10.955 --> 45:13.082
- I invited myself over here.
- Well, whatever.

45:13.157 --> 45:16.149
- I mean, I know that
must be kind of unusual.
- It's not unusual. l--

45:16.227 --> 45:18.161
I mean, I'm sure that most women
don't turn you down. [Muttering]

45:18.229 --> 45:20.629
Meredith, can we talk about
something else?

45:20.698 --> 45:23.326
Honestly, sex is the last thing
on my mind right now.

45:23.401 --> 45:25.631
- Okay, okay.
- Okay?

45:25.703 --> 45:28.866
Okay. Okay.

45:28.939 --> 45:32.500
Want a taste? I mean, l-I'm sorry
if I ruined your plans. That's all.

45:32.576 --> 45:35.511
I didn't have any plans!
I just think--

45:35.579 --> 45:38.013
You know, you've got
a few too many rules working for you...

45:38.082 --> 45:41.051
and way too many rules
workin' against me!

45:41.118 --> 45:44.315
- [Drops Spoon]
- I really like you, but--

45:44.388 --> 45:46.982
This kind of thing
is pissing me off.

45:50.394 --> 45:53.158
Maybe this wasn't such a good idea.

45:56.267 --> 45:59.395
I can't understand why you haven't had
a relationship lately.

46:02.406 --> 46:06.103
Really?
Well, that doesn't take long, does it?

46:06.177 --> 46:08.407
- What doesn't?
- I mean, you turn a guy down...

46:08.479 --> 46:11.607
a-and wham, he just metamorphoses
into an anger ball.

46:11.682 --> 46:13.843
- "Anger ball"?
- See?

46:13.918 --> 46:17.354
All I said was
I have a good imagination.

46:17.421 --> 46:20.618
- I wasn't talking about sex.
- Really.

46:20.691 --> 46:23.683
I've had enough... sex.

46:23.761 --> 46:25.695
Mostly with women
I didn't really like...

46:25.763 --> 46:29.028
a-and probably
didn't really like me.

46:31.535 --> 46:33.730
Call me nuts, man,
but l-- I like you.

46:33.804 --> 46:36.136
And...

46:36.207 --> 46:39.699
yeah, if something happens between us,
sex will probably enter into it.

46:39.777 --> 46:43.577
But not until you break
the brick wall down around yourself...

46:43.647 --> 46:46.980
and certainly not tonight.

46:49.954 --> 46:51.888
Are you finished?

46:52.990 --> 46:55.458
- Yeah.
- I'll show you out.

46:57.061 --> 47:00.622
- What!
- Look, this is exactly
what I don't want.

47:00.698 --> 47:02.598
- Somebody being straight with you?
- Yes!

47:02.666 --> 47:05.897
Yes, yes.

47:05.970 --> 47:10.498
You know what, Trent?
I do not have the stamina for this.

47:10.574 --> 47:12.508
I don't.

47:12.576 --> 47:15.511
- Meredith, we haven't
even started anything.
- You know what?

47:15.579 --> 47:19.242
We're not going to.

47:19.316 --> 47:22.979
Because let me just jump ahead
to the inevitable. Okay?

47:24.054 --> 47:25.988
We get together.

47:26.056 --> 47:29.025
You hurt me.
It ends badly.

47:29.093 --> 47:33.257
That's a really depressing way
to look at a fledgling relationship.

47:33.330 --> 47:36.697
Well, there's nothing
fledgling about it.

47:36.767 --> 47:39.668
And honestly, that is
the only viewpoint that I have.

47:42.640 --> 47:46.440
Then I feel sorry for you,
Meredith, because I didn't
come over here to hurt you.

47:52.082 --> 47:55.449
- I hope Barley likes Italian.
- He does.

48:01.992 --> 48:05.325
- [Sighs]
- [Door Slams]

48:05.396 --> 48:07.330
[Phone Ringing]

48:10.100 --> 48:11.829
What?

48:23.647 --> 48:26.081
- [TV Playing, Indistinct]
- What are you watching?

48:26.150 --> 48:28.414
Midnight Lace.

48:28.485 --> 48:31.921
Ah. Doris Day.

48:31.989 --> 48:34.583
Oh, yeah. That's the one
where she thinks she's going crazy...

48:34.658 --> 48:37.354
but it's really her husband
that's driving her to suicide...

48:37.428 --> 48:39.419
for her money.

48:39.496 --> 48:42.021
[Turns Off TV]
Well, thank you, Paul!

48:42.099 --> 48:45.535
Why don't you just go-- go find
a theater that's showing Citizen Kane...

48:45.603 --> 48:48.197
and yell out
"Rosebud is a sled"?

48:48.272 --> 48:50.740
- I'm sorry.
I thought you'd seen it before.
- Well, I hadn't.

48:50.808 --> 48:53.174
I mean, I thought we'd seen it before.

48:53.244 --> 48:55.838
Perhaps you have me confused
with Wendy.

48:55.913 --> 48:57.847
So that's what this is all about.

48:57.915 --> 49:02.375
- What "this"? There isn't any "this."
- No? No "this"?

49:02.453 --> 49:04.512
Do you normally speak
through clenched teeth?

49:04.588 --> 49:07.421
I'm not speaking any different
than normal.

49:07.491 --> 49:10.051
- Differently.
- Oh!

49:21.035 --> 49:22.969
You are being idiotic.

49:23.037 --> 49:27.633
Well, you wouldn't want me to act
any different than normal, would you?

49:27.708 --> 49:31.075
- "Differently."
- This isn't exactly what I had in mind.

49:31.145 --> 49:33.636
- Do you still see her?
- Who?

49:33.714 --> 49:36.547
"Who?" Who?
Doris Day!

49:36.617 --> 49:39.142
Oh, you mean Wendy.

49:39.220 --> 49:41.814
You thought I didn't know,
didn't you?

49:41.889 --> 49:45.484
You think the little woman doesn't know
when her husband has an affair.

49:45.559 --> 49:50.223
Hannah, it was 25 years ago,
and it wasn't an affair.

49:50.298 --> 49:52.493
Oh, don't insult my intelligence.

49:52.566 --> 49:56.161
Your intelligence, at the moment,
is in serious doubt.

49:56.237 --> 49:59.001
- Screw you!
- Hannah.

49:59.073 --> 50:01.564
Paul.

50:05.212 --> 50:07.840
[Slams, Locks Door]

50:07.915 --> 50:12.181
[Jiggles Door Knob] Do you really want
to talk about this? Hmm?

50:12.253 --> 50:17.452
Because if you do, I'll tell you
everything you want to know.

50:17.525 --> 50:20.460
You might start
by being honest with me.

50:20.528 --> 50:23.326
- It wasn't an affair?
- It wasn't.

50:23.397 --> 50:27.993
- I never slept with Wendy.
- Oh, please! [Slams Door]

50:28.069 --> 50:30.469
Hey, calm down.
You're overwrought.

50:30.538 --> 50:32.802
I am perfectly wrought.

50:32.873 --> 50:35.967
Given the circumstances,
I'm even a bit underwrought.

50:36.043 --> 50:38.807
- There's no such word.
- There is now.

50:40.715 --> 50:44.651
Do you want to know...
why I didn't sleep with Wendy?

50:47.054 --> 50:48.180
[Door Opening]

50:50.758 --> 50:53.852
I am, as they say, all ears.

50:53.928 --> 50:57.364
Well, I never
slept with Wendy...

50:57.431 --> 51:00.423
because I was
too much in love with her.

51:02.837 --> 51:04.771
Oh.

51:09.610 --> 51:12.807
You couldn't have died
without telling me that?

51:18.419 --> 51:20.649
% [Pop]

51:20.721 --> 51:24.316
% [Continues]

51:24.392 --> 51:26.485
- [Sighs]
- [Knocking]

51:26.560 --> 51:28.824
- % [Continues]
- [Man] Keenan? You going out?

51:28.896 --> 51:32.491
- % [Continues]
- Yes, Dad.

51:36.904 --> 51:39.668
Hi. I know for this technically
not to be a date...

51:39.740 --> 51:43.176
we should have gone dutch, but the
tickets were selling out so fast, so--

51:43.244 --> 51:46.270
What would you have done
if I didn't show up?

51:46.347 --> 51:48.838
Um, well, after I recovered from
the supreme disappointment...

51:48.916 --> 51:51.510
and picked up the pieces
of my fractured ego...

51:51.585 --> 51:55.351
I would have run down the escalator and
invited the guy standing on the corner.

51:55.423 --> 51:57.357
You know, the one holding the sign.

51:57.425 --> 52:00.019
The one that says,
"Will work for food"?

52:00.094 --> 52:03.359
Or a movie.
You should have read the fine print.

52:06.767 --> 52:09.531
% I'll plant my own tree %

52:09.603 --> 52:13.300
% And I'll make it grow %

52:13.374 --> 52:16.138
% My tree will not be %

52:16.210 --> 52:20.112
% Just one in a row %

52:20.181 --> 52:23.150
% My tree will offer shade %

52:23.217 --> 52:27.017
% When strangers go by %

52:27.087 --> 52:29.317
% If you're a stranger %

52:29.390 --> 52:31.654
% Brother, well, so am I %

52:31.725 --> 52:33.693
Gin gimlet, rocks.

52:33.761 --> 52:35.695
Make it two.

52:35.763 --> 52:37.822
- I'm Lana.
- Hugh.

52:37.898 --> 52:40.526
[Chuckles]
I haven't seen you here before.

52:40.601 --> 52:44.332
- Well, how do you know that?
- Honey, you sounded
like John Wayne in a bathhouse.

52:44.405 --> 52:47.340
[Imitating John Wayne]
Well, as a matter of fact,
this is my first time here.

52:47.408 --> 52:50.673
[Laughs] I'm 28 years old,
in case you're wondering.

52:50.744 --> 52:53.508
And that's in real years,
not Heather Locklear years.

52:53.581 --> 52:55.549
I'm also a drag queen.

52:55.616 --> 52:59.518
- I think I figured that out.
- Well, I just didn't want
there to be any misunderstanding.

52:59.587 --> 53:01.817
This ain't no disco, and I don't want
no Crying Game confusion.

53:01.889 --> 53:04.687
I want it understood up front,
I may be a fabulous-looking broad...

53:04.758 --> 53:06.692
but I've got a penis.

53:06.760 --> 53:09.695
- So do l.
- Well, then we'll get along just fine.

53:09.763 --> 53:13.790
So you come on and tell Lana what
the fuck you're doing in this place.

53:13.868 --> 53:18.134
Um... I had a...
fight with my wife.

53:18.205 --> 53:20.639
- Old story.
- Well, it's an old story...

53:20.708 --> 53:23.302
but it's a newish twist.

53:23.377 --> 53:26.312
"Newish twist"? Damn, that's a bitch
to say with my sibilance.

53:26.380 --> 53:28.314
I'll have to roll that one
around my tongue later.

53:28.382 --> 53:32.716
Unless you got better ideas.
"Newish twist." Continue.

53:32.786 --> 53:37.086
My wife discovered
I was stepping out on her.

53:37.157 --> 53:39.057
[Yawns]
When does the "newish" part come in?

53:39.126 --> 53:41.060
That one's older
than Lauren Bacall.

53:41.128 --> 53:44.495
Well, I-I cheated on my wife...

53:44.565 --> 53:47.159
with her brother.

53:47.234 --> 53:51.830
[Puts Down Glass]
Make that a double, and keep 'em coming.

53:51.906 --> 53:54.340
% It's impossible
Tell you right now %

53:54.408 --> 53:56.876
% If I tried it
I'd never know how %

53:56.944 --> 54:00.311
- % [Continues]
- He's her younger brother. Sam.

54:00.381 --> 54:03.179
I knew he was gay, of course.
You can always tell.

54:03.250 --> 54:05.514
It's called "gay-dar."

54:05.586 --> 54:08.180
- I'm not gay or anything.
- No, no, no.

54:08.255 --> 54:10.189
Of course not.

54:10.257 --> 54:13.192
It's just something about him.

54:13.260 --> 54:17.526
He always looked at me
like he could see right inside me...

54:17.598 --> 54:19.532
to my true soul.

54:31.545 --> 54:34.981
- Don't look at me
with that tone of voice.
- [Scoffs]

54:35.049 --> 54:37.142
[Sighs]

54:38.552 --> 54:42.921
Let me...
try and explain this.

54:42.990 --> 54:46.983
Wendy came along at a time
when I needed somebody.

54:47.061 --> 54:52.829
If this is supposed to be making me
feel better, you're failing miserably.

54:52.900 --> 54:54.993
It didn't mean
that I didn't love you.

54:55.069 --> 54:57.264
In fact, it meant that I did love you.

54:57.338 --> 54:59.499
Well...

54:59.573 --> 55:04.169
you seem to have been loving
a lot of people right about then:

55:04.244 --> 55:06.508
the kids...

55:06.580 --> 55:09.515
Wendy, me.

55:09.583 --> 55:11.574
Anybody else?

55:11.652 --> 55:14.120
Hannah, we've been married
for 40 years.

55:14.188 --> 55:16.952
There were some rough times.
Admit it.

55:17.024 --> 55:19.458
Oh, I admit it.

55:19.526 --> 55:22.461
This is one of them.

55:22.529 --> 55:25.794
You know I spent a lot of time
that summer with Wendy.

55:25.866 --> 55:29.131
Our production company
did throw us together.

55:29.203 --> 55:31.797
If I remember correctly, I hired her.

55:31.872 --> 55:36.309
Right. We were launching
your first show.

55:36.377 --> 55:39.813
And... well, Wendy was a big help.

55:39.880 --> 55:41.939
Oh, I'll bet.

55:45.552 --> 55:48.316
- Were you really in love with her?
- Yes.

55:48.389 --> 55:52.325
Yeah, I was.
I remember wishing then that I wasn't.

55:52.393 --> 55:54.588
I couldn't think straight
for a whole year.

55:56.230 --> 55:59.996
- That's when you lost all that weight.
- Yes.

56:00.067 --> 56:03.833
- I thought it was overwork.
- It was Wendy.

56:06.407 --> 56:08.841
- I didn't love you any less.
- Oh, don't.

56:08.909 --> 56:11.002
- I didn't.
- Don't.

56:11.078 --> 56:14.707
I just loved her...

56:14.782 --> 56:16.716
differently.

56:16.784 --> 56:18.718
Differently.

56:18.786 --> 56:20.720
Mm-hmm.

56:23.023 --> 56:25.651
And you really didn't
sleep with her?

56:25.726 --> 56:27.660
No.

56:29.029 --> 56:31.793
[Sighs]
Of course not.

56:31.865 --> 56:35.130
And you didn't want
to sleep with her?

56:35.202 --> 56:37.796
Oh, good God, yes, I did.

56:40.541 --> 56:44.705
You bastard.
You bastard!

56:44.778 --> 56:46.803
- [Muttering]
- What--

56:46.880 --> 56:49.144
- Hey!
- Just don't touch me! Just--

56:49.216 --> 56:51.810
I've had it!

56:51.885 --> 56:53.944
- Well, you did ask.
- [Huffs]

56:57.224 --> 56:59.158
Oh, boy.

57:10.738 --> 57:14.265
A couple times during the movie
I thought you ducked out on me.

57:14.341 --> 57:16.275
I had to use the bathroom.

57:16.343 --> 57:19.608
Well, at crucial times like
these, you should inform a girl
about having a small bladder.

57:19.680 --> 57:22.444
It saves her
from abandonment fantasies.

57:22.516 --> 57:25.952
Would it help at all
if I told you I didn't sit down to pee?

57:26.019 --> 57:28.613
In this theater,
I don't sit down to pee.

57:36.196 --> 57:38.130
Going dancing?

57:38.198 --> 57:40.291
Maybe.

57:40.367 --> 57:42.631
I'm not asking
to go with you, you know.

57:42.703 --> 57:45.137
We can take this slowly.

57:45.205 --> 57:48.299
Joan, this isn't anything.

57:48.375 --> 57:51.970
It's not anything now,
and it won't be anything ever.

57:52.045 --> 57:57.312
Wow. Message received.
End of date.

57:57.384 --> 57:59.648
- I'll walk you to your car.
- Oh, that's so sweet.

57:59.720 --> 58:01.654
That is so sweet.
He never wants to see her again...

58:01.722 --> 58:04.316
but he doesn't want her to be
dismembered in the underground parking.

58:04.391 --> 58:08.327
- Where are you parked?
- On the "Artist formerly
known as Prince" level.

58:16.537 --> 58:19.267
Which one is yours?

58:19.339 --> 58:21.933
The V.W. in space 23.

58:22.009 --> 58:25.445
Uh, there's nothing in space 23.

58:25.512 --> 58:27.446
Really?

58:31.351 --> 58:33.979
Shit!
Shit!

58:34.054 --> 58:37.285
Shit! Shit!
Shit! Shit!

58:37.357 --> 58:39.723
Shit!
I cannot believe this!

58:39.793 --> 58:41.727
I cannot believe this!

58:41.795 --> 58:43.729
Maybe you remembered wrong. Maybe
you're on the Rolling Stones level.

58:43.797 --> 58:46.231
- No!
- The Madonna level?

58:46.300 --> 58:50.396
- I wouldn't be caught dead
on the Madonna level.
- We'll call the police.

58:50.470 --> 58:54.463
- I'm sure they'll be able to find it.
- I can't fucking believe this!

58:56.043 --> 58:58.511
My parents bought me that car.

58:58.579 --> 59:00.513
Joan, don't--

59:00.581 --> 59:02.515
What?
Don't what?

59:02.583 --> 59:05.780
Don't cry?
I don't fucking cry.

59:05.853 --> 59:07.787
It's something
of a thing with me.

59:10.324 --> 59:18.993
%

59:19.066 --> 59:21.330
It's very... nice.

59:21.401 --> 59:26.202
It's a hole, but it suits
me and Blanche just dandy.

59:26.273 --> 59:28.070
- Speaking of Blanche--
- [Howls]

59:28.141 --> 59:30.701
- Jesus!
- [Hisses]

59:30.777 --> 59:34.110
- [Joan] You scared her.
- That's the ugliest cat I've ever seen.

59:34.181 --> 59:37.014
- She's an angel.
- She only has one eye.

59:37.084 --> 59:41.248
Yeah, but it's her good one. Come on,
Blanche. That mean man won't hurt you.

59:41.321 --> 59:43.221
Um, I should--
I should be going.

59:43.290 --> 59:44.814
