I have a wife.
Did you know that?

01:17:14.307 --> 01:17:16.605
I don't think that
we like each other very much.

01:17:18.711 --> 01:17:21.236
Is that something
to smile about?

01:17:23.683 --> 01:17:26.777
Well, it's just that my wife--
She, um...

01:17:26.852 --> 01:17:29.844
doesn't think that I have
much of an imagination.

01:17:29.922 --> 01:17:32.152
If she only knew.

01:17:33.693 --> 01:17:36.457
If she only knew a lot of things.

01:17:36.529 --> 01:17:39.259
If I only knew a lot of things.

01:17:39.332 --> 01:17:41.266
Such as?

01:17:43.202 --> 01:17:45.136
Where to start:

01:17:45.204 --> 01:17:48.469
with myself...

01:17:48.541 --> 01:17:51.704
with my wife.

01:18:04.490 --> 01:18:07.482
They got it back.

01:18:07.560 --> 01:18:10.290
They got what back?

01:18:10.363 --> 01:18:12.297
The police. Your car.

01:18:12.365 --> 01:18:15.766
Oh, right. Yeah.

01:18:15.835 --> 01:18:17.769
Keenan, listen, I'm--

01:18:17.837 --> 01:18:21.102
You don't have to say anything. l-l told
you because I wanted to tell you.

01:18:23.342 --> 01:18:26.937
I wanted to because for
the first time in a long time
I wish things were different.

01:18:27.013 --> 01:18:29.709
- They can be.
- No, they can't.

01:18:37.857 --> 01:18:40.052
Well, none of this means
you can't love.

01:18:40.126 --> 01:18:43.459
Joan, it means exactly that.
It doesn't mean anything else.

01:18:43.529 --> 01:18:45.997
I don't believe that for a second,
that you can't love.

01:18:46.065 --> 01:18:48.124
- I can't.
- Stop saying that.

01:18:48.200 --> 01:18:52.136
It's the only thing I can say
to make you understand.

01:18:53.739 --> 01:18:57.800
This may sound corny, but--

01:18:57.877 --> 01:19:01.313
But you don't want me.

01:19:01.380 --> 01:19:03.348
I-I'm damaged goods.

01:19:03.416 --> 01:19:08.479
For Christ's sake,
we're all damaged goods.

01:19:08.554 --> 01:19:12.490
I'm wandering around through life
with hardly any purpose or goal at all.

01:19:12.558 --> 01:19:14.992
I don't know what
I'm doing half the time...

01:19:15.061 --> 01:19:17.325
but I know that I can love.

01:19:17.396 --> 01:19:19.660
I know that I can love you.
I know that I do love you.

01:19:19.732 --> 01:19:22.929
- I won't let you love me.
- Why?

01:19:25.571 --> 01:19:28.665
[Voice Cracking]
I won't let you love me because...

01:19:33.245 --> 01:19:35.679
because I love you.

01:19:37.483 --> 01:19:39.849
[Crying]
You love me?

01:19:39.919 --> 01:19:41.910
- Can I go?
- No!

01:19:41.987 --> 01:19:43.921
[Car Doors Lock]

01:19:43.989 --> 01:19:46.355
Do you know how long I have waited
for somebody I care about...

01:19:46.425 --> 01:19:48.825
to say that they love me
and for me to actually believe them?

01:19:48.894 --> 01:19:51.021
And if you think you're getting out
of this car, you're insane!

01:19:51.097 --> 01:19:53.190
It will never work.

01:19:54.600 --> 01:19:56.534
It's already working.

01:19:56.602 --> 01:19:59.696
It's working.
[Crying]

01:20:05.945 --> 01:20:08.345
I thought--
I thought you didn't cry.

01:20:08.414 --> 01:20:10.541
I thought you didn't date.

01:20:10.616 --> 01:20:14.484
Surprise, I'm crying...

01:20:14.553 --> 01:20:16.646
and this is very much a date.

01:20:16.722 --> 01:20:21.159
It's unconventional, perhaps,
but it's the best date I've ever had.

01:20:30.069 --> 01:20:33.004
I can't!
[Lunges At Car Controls]

01:20:33.072 --> 01:20:37.168
No-- Keenan, please!
Please don't go!

01:20:37.243 --> 01:20:41.839
- [Panting]
- [Joan Crying]

01:20:41.914 --> 01:20:46.851
[Continues Crying]

01:20:50.756 --> 01:20:53.452
[Whimpering]

01:20:56.262 --> 01:20:58.196
Hey!

01:20:58.264 --> 01:21:01.859
Hi, buddies.
How are you?

01:21:01.934 --> 01:21:04.027
Who's a good boy?
Who's a good boy?

01:21:10.943 --> 01:21:13.309
You're home early tonight.

01:21:14.547 --> 01:21:16.811
You as well.

01:21:16.882 --> 01:21:19.544
Well, inventory's almost over.

01:21:19.618 --> 01:21:22.644
How is your improv class?

01:21:22.721 --> 01:21:25.383
It finished tonight.

01:21:25.457 --> 01:21:28.324
I thought you had
another couple days.

01:21:28.394 --> 01:21:34.196
Well, I should say that
I finished tonight.

01:21:34.266 --> 01:21:36.427
It wasn't what you had in mind?

01:21:36.502 --> 01:21:38.436
Ultimately, no.

01:21:38.504 --> 01:21:43.999
Well... I'm sure you'll find
something you enjoy.

01:21:47.580 --> 01:21:49.514
I mean, to keep you occupied.

01:21:50.950 --> 01:21:53.510
I'm going to try.

01:22:01.093 --> 01:22:03.357
[Laughs]

01:22:03.429 --> 01:22:06.023
Well, as the British say,
I'm knackered.

01:22:08.267 --> 01:22:11.134
You know what Saturday is, don't you?

01:22:11.203 --> 01:22:13.137
I do.

01:22:13.205 --> 01:22:15.639
Okay.

01:22:15.708 --> 01:22:18.142
It might be easier if we meet there.

01:22:18.210 --> 01:22:20.804
Whatever's easier.

01:22:20.879 --> 01:22:24.645
All right. Did you feed the dogs?
You gave them their pills?

01:22:24.717 --> 01:22:28.483
Okay. Well, don't forget to turn out
the light before you come to bed.

01:22:28.554 --> 01:22:31.318
- I won't.
- Tomorrow's trash day.

01:22:38.230 --> 01:22:42.564
[Doctor] There isn't much more
we can do, except ease the pain.

01:22:43.669 --> 01:22:46.160
All right.

01:22:46.238 --> 01:22:48.502
Ease the pain.

01:23:02.254 --> 01:23:04.518
- Mom?
- Yes, honey.

01:23:04.590 --> 01:23:06.581
- Mom?
- I'm here.

01:23:06.659 --> 01:23:09.355
Wh-Where's Jack?

01:23:09.428 --> 01:23:13.023
- He's not here.
- He was just here a minute ago.

01:23:13.098 --> 01:23:15.999
- No?
- No.

01:23:16.068 --> 01:23:20.300
- It was... you who were here.
- Yes, I'm here.

01:23:20.372 --> 01:23:24.866
- You are here, aren't you?
- Yes, I'm here.

01:23:27.379 --> 01:23:29.643
Tell me about death.

01:23:46.565 --> 01:23:49.500
Remember a long time ago...

01:23:49.568 --> 01:23:52.059
when you were still
inside my belly...

01:23:52.137 --> 01:23:55.834
and the contractions began?

01:23:57.910 --> 01:24:01.243
Well, they're beginning again.

01:24:01.313 --> 01:24:05.181
- Read me that story.
- What story?

01:24:05.250 --> 01:24:08.185
The one with the rabbit
and the rocking chair.

01:24:11.590 --> 01:24:13.751
- Good Night, Moon?
- Yeah.

01:24:13.826 --> 01:24:17.284
I like the ending.
Read me the ending.

01:24:34.546 --> 01:24:38.141
Good night, comb.

01:24:38.217 --> 01:24:41.448
Good night, brush.

01:24:41.520 --> 01:24:43.988
Good night, nobody.

01:24:46.558 --> 01:24:49.493
Good night, mush.

01:24:52.398 --> 01:24:57.335
Good night to the old lady
whispering hush.

01:24:59.405 --> 01:25:01.339
Good night, stars.

01:25:03.075 --> 01:25:07.671
Good night... air.

01:25:10.916 --> 01:25:14.283
Good night, noises...

01:25:17.523 --> 01:25:19.457
everywhere.

01:25:28.400 --> 01:25:33.337
[Crying]

01:26:12.411 --> 01:26:17.280
Do you ever wonder if
while we spend all this time
anthropomorphizing our animals...

01:26:17.349 --> 01:26:19.783
maybe they're just
anthropomorphizing us?

01:26:19.852 --> 01:26:21.877
- [Blanche Purring]
- Hmm.

01:26:21.954 --> 01:26:25.446
I didn't think so.
Who? Keenan?

01:26:25.524 --> 01:26:29.290
No. Trust me,
I'll never hear from him again.

01:26:29.361 --> 01:26:33.957
Well, I'm sorry to disappoint you,
but I'm fresh out of jokes.

01:26:34.032 --> 01:26:37.468
What, is that a rhetorical question?
Why is my life so complicated?

01:26:37.536 --> 01:26:41.302
Gee, I don't know.
Why is your life so fucking simple?

01:26:41.373 --> 01:26:43.967
- [Knocking]
- Hold on. There's someone at the door.

01:26:44.042 --> 01:26:46.704
Well, I don't know until I answer it,
do l? Yeah, I'll ask who it is.

01:26:46.778 --> 01:26:48.712
Hold on.
Yeah.

01:26:52.985 --> 01:26:54.646
Hi.

01:26:54.720 --> 01:26:56.813
Hi.

01:26:56.889 --> 01:27:00.222
Um, I'm just on the phone.
I'm gonna wrap it up, okay?

01:27:02.895 --> 01:27:04.886
[Closes Door]

01:27:10.469 --> 01:27:12.403
M.C.I.

01:27:12.471 --> 01:27:14.735
They're geniuses at tricking you
into conversation.

01:27:14.806 --> 01:27:17.536
I can't stop thinking about you.

01:27:17.609 --> 01:27:19.440
I love conversations that
start with the guy saying...

01:27:19.511 --> 01:27:21.376
"l can't stop thinking about you."

01:27:21.446 --> 01:27:24.074
Mind you, I've never actually
been on the receiving end
of any of those conversations.

01:27:24.149 --> 01:27:26.083
Just looking at you
makes me happy.

01:27:26.151 --> 01:27:28.278
I have--
I have to sit down.

01:27:31.256 --> 01:27:35.625
When we're together,
whether or not I show it...

01:27:35.694 --> 01:27:40.188
[Groans] I just can't wait to hear
the next words out of your mouth.

01:27:40.265 --> 01:27:44.395
But right now I need to ask you
to do something for me.

01:27:44.469 --> 01:27:46.403
Anything.

01:27:46.471 --> 01:27:50.134
Shut up.
Just for a moment.

01:27:50.208 --> 01:27:52.938
I've been-- I've been thinking about
what you said last night.

01:27:54.546 --> 01:27:58.312
I have no idea
why you're so relentless...

01:27:58.383 --> 01:28:00.977
particularly, given the arsenal
of defenses I've thrown at you.

01:28:01.053 --> 01:28:02.987
But...

01:28:04.723 --> 01:28:10.628
no matter how hard I've tried to block
out everything that you've said...

01:28:10.696 --> 01:28:12.721
the message has been received.

01:28:16.168 --> 01:28:19.433
In a place inside me
that I thought had died.

01:28:20.505 --> 01:28:23.235
But it hasn't.

01:28:25.010 --> 01:28:28.776
And that place inside me
is alive and well.

01:28:32.351 --> 01:28:34.444
I can't make any promises...

01:28:34.519 --> 01:28:36.953
but...

01:28:37.022 --> 01:28:39.786
I'd like to try and be with you.

01:28:42.427 --> 01:28:46.454
It won't be easy,
but I'd like to try.

01:28:46.531 --> 01:28:48.761
Can I say something?

01:28:56.942 --> 01:29:00.639
You're right.
It won't be easy, but...

01:29:00.712 --> 01:29:03.647
[Laughing]

01:29:03.715 --> 01:29:05.910
that's okay.

01:29:07.386 --> 01:29:11.550
I want to be with you, but,
you have to understand, l, um--

01:29:11.623 --> 01:29:13.648
- We can't--
- Have sex.

01:29:13.725 --> 01:29:17.161
It may not be the conventional wisdom,
but it's the only way I can do this.

01:29:17.229 --> 01:29:19.356
At least for the time being.

01:29:20.732 --> 01:29:22.700
That's not a problem?

01:29:22.768 --> 01:29:28.331
When was having sex
or not having sex not a problem?

01:29:28.407 --> 01:29:33.174
To be honest, it's gonna
be difficult not to express
physically what I feel for you...

01:29:33.245 --> 01:29:37.648
but...
we can look for other ways.

01:29:37.716 --> 01:29:42.813
There's nothing wrong
with holding each other. Hmm?

01:29:42.888 --> 01:29:45.379
Nothing at all.

01:29:45.457 --> 01:29:47.391
And sleeping with each other.

01:29:47.459 --> 01:29:49.393
We can do that.

01:29:49.461 --> 01:29:52.225
And... loving each other forever.

01:29:53.765 --> 01:29:56.859
- What did I ever do to deserve you?
- [Laughs]

01:29:56.935 --> 01:30:01.201
Usually that line is screamed at me
by somebody running out the door...

01:30:01.273 --> 01:30:05.039
not standing in front
of me and staying.

01:30:05.110 --> 01:30:07.874
It makes for a nice change.

01:30:07.946 --> 01:30:11.712
% Lay it down, child %

01:30:14.419 --> 01:30:16.819
% Lay it down, child %

01:30:16.888 --> 01:30:22.485
% And walk into this room %

01:30:24.396 --> 01:30:26.830
[Joan Sighs, Giggles]

01:30:29.000 --> 01:30:30.934
[Trent] Ah, flowers.

01:30:31.002 --> 01:30:33.835
How thoughtful.

01:30:33.905 --> 01:30:36.999
Whoo. We like the same merlot.

01:30:37.075 --> 01:30:40.010
It's actually the very same bottle
that you brought to my house.

01:30:40.078 --> 01:30:42.569
[Laughs] Excellent.

01:30:42.647 --> 01:30:44.672
Come on in.

01:30:44.750 --> 01:30:46.684
Wow.

01:30:51.923 --> 01:30:55.518
- You're wondering where dinner is.
- Uh, I must say.

01:30:55.594 --> 01:30:57.858
I have a little confession to make.

01:30:57.929 --> 01:31:01.194
I invited you to dinner at my house,
but I can't cook.

01:31:01.266 --> 01:31:03.359
- Oh.
- [Doorbell Rings]

01:31:03.435 --> 01:31:05.369
- [Laughs]
- I can order delivery.

01:31:05.437 --> 01:31:07.530
All right.

01:31:07.606 --> 01:31:09.870
Chinese food is my specialty.

01:31:19.551 --> 01:31:21.985
What are we making?

01:31:22.053 --> 01:31:24.146
Some hemlock.

01:31:24.222 --> 01:31:26.747
Oh, please, don't deprive
the kids of their mother.

01:31:26.825 --> 01:31:31.159
- Oh, I'm not making it for me.
- Ah, that's the Hannah that I know.

01:31:31.229 --> 01:31:35.097
Well, you seem to know me
a lot better than I know you.

01:31:35.167 --> 01:31:37.499
You know that's not true.

01:31:37.569 --> 01:31:42.871
Do you remember what you told
the kids about falling in love?

01:31:44.242 --> 01:31:46.676
- No.
- Well, I do.

01:31:46.745 --> 01:31:50.181
You said that the wonderful thing
about falling in love...

01:31:50.248 --> 01:31:56.016
is that you learn everything
about that person, and so quickly.

01:31:56.087 --> 01:31:58.021
And if it's true love...

01:31:58.089 --> 01:32:01.525
then you start to see yourself
through their eyes...

01:32:01.593 --> 01:32:03.527
and it brings out
the best in you...

01:32:03.595 --> 01:32:08.032
and it's almost as if you're
falling in love with yourself.

01:32:08.099 --> 01:32:11.364
- I said that?
- Mm-hmm.

01:32:11.436 --> 01:32:15.736
Well, 25 years ago,
I needed to feel that again.

01:32:15.807 --> 01:32:19.140
Feel that I was worth loving.

01:32:19.211 --> 01:32:21.645
Because somehow I knew...

01:32:21.713 --> 01:32:26.047
that would be my last time
to have that particular feeling.

01:32:27.886 --> 01:32:31.481
- You couldn't have it with me?
- Oh, I did have it with you...

01:32:31.556 --> 01:32:33.649
but I'd forgotten it.

01:32:33.725 --> 01:32:36.489
I hadn't forgotten
why I loved you...

01:32:36.561 --> 01:32:39.394
but I'd forgotten
why you loved me.

01:32:41.399 --> 01:32:43.333
[Laughs]

01:32:43.401 --> 01:32:46.165
And Wendy made me remember...

01:32:46.238 --> 01:32:49.833
that I was a pretty terrific fellow.

01:32:49.908 --> 01:32:52.342
Bully for Wendy.

01:32:52.410 --> 01:32:56.346
But I knew that
I couldn't sleep with her.

01:32:56.414 --> 01:32:58.041
Why?

01:32:58.116 --> 01:33:02.280
Because I would have left you...
and the kids.

01:33:12.931 --> 01:33:15.798
What are we thinking?

01:33:15.867 --> 01:33:18.461
Hot liquid and facial burns.

01:33:18.536 --> 01:33:20.800
Oh.

01:33:20.872 --> 01:33:25.969
Remember the day
Wendy left the company...

01:33:26.044 --> 01:33:28.979
- and went to Seattle?
- Yes.

01:33:29.047 --> 01:33:31.140
I thought for a while
you might go with her.

01:33:31.216 --> 01:33:34.151
Me too, but I didn't.

01:33:37.889 --> 01:33:40.483
When I came home that day...

01:33:40.558 --> 01:33:44.654
I realized that I was
more in love with you...

01:33:44.729 --> 01:33:46.993
than ever before.

01:33:48.733 --> 01:33:52.169
How did that thunderbolt strike you?

01:33:52.237 --> 01:33:55.331
Because I'd made a choice.

01:33:56.574 --> 01:34:00.010
I took one look at you...

01:34:00.078 --> 01:34:04.674
and I knew I'd made
the right choice.

01:34:04.749 --> 01:34:07.013
I know that sounds daft...

01:34:07.085 --> 01:34:10.851
but my love for somebody else...

01:34:10.922 --> 01:34:13.789
made me love you more...

01:34:13.858 --> 01:34:18.124
because I sought...

01:34:18.196 --> 01:34:20.130
to reclaim myself.

01:34:21.866 --> 01:34:24.130
And, Hannah...

01:34:24.202 --> 01:34:27.137
you're still the right choice.

01:34:30.208 --> 01:34:33.143
We made a child that day.

01:34:33.211 --> 01:34:35.145
We did, indeed.

01:34:35.213 --> 01:34:37.807
Our Jo-Jo.

01:34:37.882 --> 01:34:41.477
Yeah. We did, indeed.

01:34:47.459 --> 01:34:50.223
[Hannah Sighs]

01:34:50.362 --> 01:34:53.331
[Pouring Wine]

01:34:53.398 --> 01:34:56.834
%
[Sighs]

01:34:56.901 --> 01:34:59.495
- Cheers. [Clinks Glass]
- Thank you.

01:34:59.571 --> 01:35:02.165
% [Continues]

01:35:02.240 --> 01:35:05.175
Trent...

01:35:05.243 --> 01:35:07.302
I have to tell you something.

01:35:07.379 --> 01:35:10.837
Oh, this doesn't begin with
"Trent, you are a nice guy," does it?

01:35:10.915 --> 01:35:13.213
- No.
- Whew.

01:35:13.284 --> 01:35:16.947
The problem I have with you--

01:35:18.356 --> 01:35:20.620
We have problems?

01:35:24.529 --> 01:35:28.295
The problem I have with you...

01:35:28.366 --> 01:35:31.130
is that I'm attracted to you.

01:35:33.204 --> 01:35:35.172
And that's a problem?

01:35:37.242 --> 01:35:40.370
It is for me.

01:35:40.445 --> 01:35:43.642
It's, um--

01:35:44.883 --> 01:35:46.976
Gosh, this is so embarrassing.
[Sighs]

01:35:47.052 --> 01:35:48.986
- What?
- [Clears Throat]

01:35:49.054 --> 01:35:51.648
Don't be embarrassed.

01:35:51.723 --> 01:35:55.318
% [Continues]

01:35:55.393 --> 01:35:58.487
I don't deal with passion well.

01:35:58.563 --> 01:36:01.657
Maybe you don't like
that loss of control.

01:36:01.733 --> 01:36:05.829
You prefer to be the director,
telling everyone what to do.

01:36:07.405 --> 01:36:09.999
It's pretty painfully obvious,
isn't it?

01:36:10.075 --> 01:36:13.272
- Somewhat painful, yes.
- [Laughs]

01:36:15.847 --> 01:36:19.112
You know, there's something
you'll find out about me.

01:36:19.184 --> 01:36:21.618
What's that?

01:36:21.686 --> 01:36:25.281
%

01:36:25.356 --> 01:36:28.120
That I take direction pretty well.

01:36:35.533 --> 01:36:38.127
% If love is a healer %

01:36:38.203 --> 01:36:42.469
% We'll be the first ones healed %

01:36:42.540 --> 01:36:46.135
% Lovers will %

01:36:46.211 --> 01:36:50.238
% You know, lovers will %

01:36:53.551 --> 01:36:55.485
- Trent.
- Yeah?

01:36:55.553 --> 01:36:58.147
You're gonna think what I'm about
to say is really ridiculous.

01:36:58.223 --> 01:37:00.987
You're worried about Barley,
and you want to go back to your place.

01:37:01.059 --> 01:37:04.995
Oh, my God.
This is way fucking spooky.

